HEADWORD: Emmarble
<hw>Em*mar"ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To turn to
marble; to harden.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou dost <qex>emmarble</qex> the proud heart.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emmenagogue</ent>⟦br⟧
